      "claim": "The paper surveys vision transformer models and organizes them into major application categories, including backbone network, high/mid-level vision, low-level vision, video processing, multimodality, and efficient transformer methods.",
      "evidence_section": "1 INTRODUCTION",
      "page": null
    },
    {
      "claim": "Vision transformer models perform similar to or better than convolutional and recurrent neural networks on a variety of visual benchmarks.",
      "evidence_section": "Abstract",
      "page": null
    },
    {
      "claim": "ViT is described as having achieved state-of-the-art performance on multiple image recognition benchmarks.",
      "evidence_section": "1 INTRODUCTION",
      "page": null
    },
    {
      "claim": "DeiT-B achieves top-1 accuracy of 83.1% on ImageNet with no external data, and 84.40% with token-based distillation.",
      "evidence_section": "3.1.1 Pure Transformer",
      "page": null
    },
    {
      "claim": "CLIP achieves 76.2% top-1 accuracy on ImageNet-1K in zero-shot transfer without using any ImageNet training labels.",
      "evidence_section": "3.5 Multi-Modal Tasks",
      "page": null
    },
    {
      "claim": "Deformable DETR achieves better performance than DETR with 10× less training cost and 1.6× faster inference speed.",
      "evidence_section": "3.2.1 Generic Object Detection",
